sentences.en: England is the largest, most populous and generally the richest section.
sentences.cn: 英格兰是最大的, 最人口多的,一般来说也是最富裕的部分.

sentences.en: He avoided the more lighted and populous streets.
sentences.cn: 他避开比较明亮和拥挤的街道.

sentences.en: Hong Kong is one of the most populous areas in the world.
sentences.cn: 香港是世界上人口最稠密的地区之一。

sentences.en: Hongkong is resplendent , floweriness, populous, extremely bright.
sentences.cn: 香港是璀璨 、 绚丽、繁华、无以复加的.

sentences.en: Humans are by far the most populous intelligent creatures in the world.
sentences.cn: 人类是迄今为止世上最足智多谋的造物.

sentences.en: Is his family very is originally rich and populous?
sentences.cn: 是他的家庭本来就很富庶?

sentences.en: Its clear atmosphere, more populous thoroughfares, and peculiar indifference struck her forcibly.
sentences.cn: 这里的空气清新, 街道更加宽阔, 还有人们之间那特有的互不关心,这一切都给她留下了深刻的印象.

sentences.en: Its route seemed interminable, through the low, brick, suburban, populous va stness.
sentences.cn: 路程好象是漫无尽头似的, 沿途经过了不少住得拥挤不堪的郊区砖砌矮房子.

sentences.en: London is the most populous area of Britain.
sentences.cn: 伦敦是英国人口最稠密的地区.

sentences.en: Mr Papandreou has also expanded his cabinet by 12, making a populous 49 - member affair.
sentences.cn: 新组建的内阁成员增加了12名, 成为人数众多的49人.

sentences.en: One of the most populous castes is that of the warrior.
sentences.cn: 人数最多的阶层之一是战士阶层(warriorcaste).

sentences.en: The atomic power stations are being sited away from populous centres.
sentences.cn: 这些电站都坐落在远离人口集中的地方.

sentences.en: The pop song is popular in the populous city.
sentences.cn: 这首流行歌曲在人口稠密的城市流行.

sentences.en: They are expected to at their most populous in the coming months.
sentences.cn: 预计在接下来几个月中,它们的数量将达到最高峰.

sentences.en: This is populous area , and a crucial market for business.
sentences.cn: 此处人口聚集, 是商家必争之地.

sentences.en: Towns in the populous trees , with hanging gardens of verdure.
sentences.cn: 熙熙攘攘的城镇, 悬吊着翠绿的园林.
